it‚Äôs inevitable and still think coinbase is best positioned to introduce this

- kyc/aml no widespread solution, ux sucks. cb already solved this and can attest it to a wallet

- chain didn‚Äôt support feature x. cb has base and can prioritize whatever necessary (clearly speed rn)

- every time money de-risks it flows out of crypto. stocks onchain means it stays in crypto (on base so cb gets more fees)
- difficult to move large sums offchain for some players. bring stocks to them instead/‚Äúcaptured market‚Äù

- warpcast has it's own approach to this with Rewards where "tipping" is engagement/free and rewarded retroactively
- reddit was strangely missing the _opposite_ side of this where people would be awarded a ton but didn't accrue much value from it

maybe warpcast can complete the flywheel where engagement gives you tips for you to engage/reward more which generates more engagement etc (approaching a decentralized version of wc rewards)
